  "body": "### What is wrong?\r\n@justindrake came up with a solution for that we can obsolete the \"empty slots\" in the collator list.\r\n\r\n### How can it be fixed\r\n1. Add another mapping for `collator_address` -> `pool_index`, the collator can use the address to look up the index by address.\r\n1. In the `withdraw` function, after the collator was removed from the pool, there's a new empty slot. Now we move the last element to fill the slot immediately and update the mapping of (1).\r\n\r\nPlease wait for the new specification with new namings.",
