    "body": "Assuming that the expected period `period=10`, lookahead length `LOOKAHEAD_LENGTH=4`, period length `PERIOD_LENGTH=5`.\r\n\r\n#456 problem became: \r\n1. When block number is 30 and the length of the collator pool is 10, one collator calls `get_eligible_proposer(shard_id=1, period=10)` and gets the eligible is the last element (`c9`) of the pool.\r\n2. When block number is 35, `collators[5]` deregisters, the length of the collator pool becomes 9. Move last element c9 to position 5.\r\n\r\n3. One collator call `get_eligible_proposer(shard_id=1, period=10)`:\r\n    1. The length of the collator pool changed..!\r\n    2. Even if we record how many collators join and exit during the lookahead ( https://github.com/ethereum/py-evm/issues/456#issuecomment-372551032) to recalculate the population of the collator pool to **a fixed number**, still, since the collator position is changed, we lost the consistency of calling `get_eligible_proposer` function during the lookahead periods.\r\n",
